  "text": "The CRD validation-to-OpenAPI pipeline flows through these stages: (1) CRD validation spec: `CustomResourceValidation` in types.go holds `JSONSchemaProps` (types_jsonschema.go), the user-provided OpenAPI v3 schema. (2) Structural schema extraction: `NewStructural()` in convert.go converts `JSONSchemaProps` into the internal `Structural` type (structural.go), then `ValidateStructural()` (validation.go) validates structural invariants, and `Unfold()` (unfold.go) expands x-kubernetes-int-or-string patterns. (3) OpenAPI schema conversion: `ToKubeOpenAPI()` (kubeopenapi.go) converts `Structural` to `spec.Schema`; for v2, `ToStructuralOpenAPIV2()` (v2/conversion.go) first strips v3-only constructs. The `generateBuilder()` and `buildKubeNative()` functions in builder.go orchestrate this, calling `BuildOpenAPIV3()`/`BuildOpenAPIV2()` to produce complete specs. (4) API server publication: The OpenAPI v2 controller (controller.go) and v3 controller (openapiv3/controller.go) watch CRD changes, call the builder, and use `MergeSpecs()` (merge.go) to aggregate CRD specs with the static API server spec, then publish via the OpenAPI service handlers.",
